{
  "text": "CTC is commonly used as a probe of membrane-bound Ca 2+ [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Sperm capacitation is associated with a specific CTC staining pattern [CITATION_3] . Since this dye also binds Sr 2+ [CITATION_4] , we could use sperm displaying the B pattern of CTC staining to follow capacitation in media containing any of the divalent cations. The rate of sperm with a B pattern was similar in cells incubated in Ca 2+ or Sr 2+ -containing media, indicating that capacitation-dependent changes related to Ca 2+ -association to the plasma membrane also take place in Sr 2+ -medium.",
